line: Good sport.  Have fun?
This thing on?  Hey, Ms. Potts. Pep.  If you find this recording, don’t post it on social media. It’s going to be a real tearjerker.
I don’t know if you’re ever going to see these.  I don’t even know if you’re still...God, I hope so. Today’s day twenty-one, no...twenty- two.

You know, if it wasn’t for the existential terror of staring into the literal void of space, I’d say I’m feeling a little better today. Infection’s run its course, thanks to the Blue Meanie back there. You’d like her.  She’s very practical.  And only a tiny bit sadistic.
The fuel cells were cracked during battle, but we figured out a way to reverse the ion charge.  Bought ourselves about 48 hours of flight time.  Problem is that was about...49 hours ago.
Which means, we’re dead in the water.  A thousand light years from the nearest 7-11.
Most of the quote-unquote ‘food’ and potable water ran out two weeks ago.
Pep, I know I said no more surprises.  But, I gotta say, I was really hoping to pull off one last one.  But it looks like...well, you know what it looks like.

Don’t feel bad about this.  I mean, actually, if you grovel for a couple weeks, and then move on with enormous guilt...I should probably lie down for a minute, rest my eyes.  Please know, when I drift off, it will be like every day lately.  I’m fine, totally fine. I’m going to dream about you.  It’s always you.
I couldn’t stop him.
Neither could we.
I lost the kid.
We...lost...
Is Pepper...?
Stay here, you stay right here-
I’m not going anywhere.
World governments are in pieces, as you can imagine.  But the parts that still work are trying to take a census.  It looks like he did what he said he was going to do.
Thanos wiped out fifty percent of all the living creatures on Earth.
Where is he now?
We don’t know.  He just opened a portal and walked through.
What’s his deal?
He’s pissed.
He thinks he failed.  Which, of course, he did.  But there’s a lot of that going around, ain’t there?
Until this second, I literally thought you were a Build-a-Bear.
We’ve been hunting Thanos for three weeks - deep space scans, satellites - we got nothing.  Tony, you fought him-
Who told you that?  I didn’t fight him, he wiped my face with a planet while a Bleecker Street magician gave away the store.  There was no fight because he’s not beatable.
Did he give you anything to go on? Clues, coordinates-
I saw this coming, few years back. Didn’t wanna believe.  I thought I was dreaming...
Tony, I need you to focus-
And I needed you, as in past tense. That trumps what you need.  It’s too late, buddy.  You know what I need?

I need a shave and a burger, not a bowl of soup. And I believe I remember telling all of you, alive and otherwise, that we needed a suit of armor around the world, whether it impacted our precious freedoms or not-
But that didn’t work out, did it?

I said we’d lose, you said we’d “do that together, too.”  Guess what, Cap, we lost, and you weren’t there.  But that’s what we do, right?  Our best work after the fact?  We’re the “Avengers”, not the “Pre-vengers-”
I’ve got nothing for ya, Cap.  No coordinates, no clues, no strategies, no options.  Zero, zip, nada.  No trust.  Here.  You take this.  You find him, you put this on, and hide.  I’m fine!
Where are you going?
Hey, hey, hang on.  We’re sort of a team here.  Between you and me, morale’s a little fragile.
Look, we realize “up there’s” more your territory, but this is our fight, too.
Where’s this garden?
When Thanos snapped his fingers, Earth become ground zero for a power surge of ridiculously cosmic proportions.  No one’s seen anything like it.
Until two days ago.
You’re saying he snapped his fingers again.  Where?
A garden.
Thanos is there.  And he just used the stones.
You know, we’d be going short- handed.
Are we saying they’re dead?  We’re using that word now?
Just like that?
Yeah.  Just like that.
If there’s even the smallest chance we can undo this, then we owe it to everyone who’s not sitting here to try.
If we do this...why would it end any differently than it did before?
I like this one.
Let’s go get that son of a bitch.
Okay, who here hasn’t been to space?
Oh, you’re gonna hate this.
This is going to work, Steve.
I know it will.  Because I don’t know what I’m going to do if it doesn’t.
Where are they?
You murdered trillions.
Where are the stones?
You used them two days ago!
No...they can’t be gone...
What did you do?
I went for the head.
What did you talk about?

That’s great.  You’ve already done the hardest part.  You took a jump, didn’t know where you’d come down. And that’s it, those little brave baby steps we’ve gotta take.  To try to make us feel whole again, to find a purpose... I went into the ice right after I met the love of my life.  Woke up seventy years later and...had to keep going.
The world’s been left in our hands. If we don’t do something with it...then Thanos might as well have killed all of us.
We boarded that “highly suspect warship” Danvers pinged.
And?
So thanks for the hot tip-
And now we smell like garbage-
You get a reading on those tremors?
Do we have a visual?  How are you handling it?
Thanks.  Carol, you’re still coming our way next month?
Getting another haircut?
All right.  Everybody keep keeping their eyes open.  This channel’s always active.  Anything goes sideways, anyone makes trouble where they shouldn’t, it comes through me.
What’s up?  Where are you?
Okay...
Could be a rival hit-
Find out where’s he going next.
I’d offer to cook you dinner but you seem sad enough already.
Come by to do your laundry?
And see a friend.
Your friend’s fine.
She leave the house today?
Nothing out there I particularly want to see.
I spotted a pod of whales coming over the bridge.
In the Hudson.
Fewer ships, cleaner water.  Just saying, there’s still a world out there.
If you’re about to tell me to look on the bright side, I’m about to hit you with a peanut butter sandwich.
Sorry.  Force of habit.
I don’t know how you do it.
I guess I don’t know how not to.
Me, neither.
I keep telling them, move on.  Grow past it.  And some of them actually do.  But not us.
If I move on, who does this?
Maybe it doesn’t need to be done.
I used to have nothing.  Then I got this.  This job, this family.  And I was better because of it.
And even though they’re gone, I’m still trying to be...better.
I think we both need to get a life.
You first.
This an old message?
It’s the front gate.
Scott, are you okay?
Only to make conversation.
I’m sorry.  It must’ve been a long five years.
Scott, what are you talking about?
Wait...wait.  Scott.  Are you talking about a time machine?
Scott, I get emails from a raccoon. Nothing’s crazy anymore.
Morgan H. Stark.  Chow time.  Want some lunch?
You should not be wearing that. It’s part of a special anniversary gift I made for Mom.  You thinking about lunch?
Where’d you find this?
You like going in the garage?  So does Daddy.  It’s all right.  Mommy never wears what I buy her.
I just want to thank you folks for dropping by.  It’s not every day one gets to contemplate biting it on an inter-dimensional timescape.
You’ve got some objections to the plan.
So you’re calling it a plan.  To me, it sounds like an exotic suicide method.  Not to mention, it’s impossible.
Tony, after what you’ve seen, is anything really impossible?

Quantum fluctuation kinda messes with the Planck Scale, which then triggers the Deutsch Proposition, can we agree on that? Chai?  In layman’s terms, it means you can cancel your Netflix subscription because you’re not coming home.
Which was a billion-to-one cosmic fluke.  Now you want to pull a- What are you calling it?
Oh, of course, a time heist, why didn’t we think of this before? Right, because it’s a pipe dream. Who are you again?
Tony, the Stones exist in the past. We could get them and bring them here.
We can snap our own fingers.  We can bring everybody back.
Or screw it up worse than he already has.
I don’t believe we would.

Gotta say it.  Sometimes I’ve missed that giddy optimism.  Sadly, all your high hopes won’t help me if there’s no logical, tangible way for me to safely execute said “time heist.”  I believe the most likely outcome would be our collective demise.
Stop, Scott.  Stop.  Are you telling me that your plan to save the universe is more than loosely based on Back to the Future?
Good.  Because that would be horseshit.  Scientifically speaking, your brother’s picture doesn’t disappear just ‘cause you went to the dance with your mom. That’s not how quantum physics works.
We have to take a stand.
We did stand.  And yet here we are.
Please don’t-
Fine.
No, Scott.  I won’t.  Even.
Good job.  I’m saved.  I wish you were coming here to ask me something else.  I’m honestly happy to see you.  If you want to stay-
Tony, I get it.  And I’m happy for you.  I am.  But this is a second chance.
Yeah, well, I got my second chance right here.  I can’t roll the dice on it.  The table is set for six. If you don’t talk shop, you’re welcome to stay for lunch.
He’s scared.
He’s not wrong.
No.  I want to do it right. We’re going to need a really big brain.
These are confusing times.
I’m kidding, I get it.  It’s crazy. I wear shirts now!
Five years ago, we got our asses kicked, right?
He’s heard.
It was worse for me.  Because I lost twice.  First Hulk lost.  Then Banner lost.  Then we all lost.
No one blamed you, Bruce.
I did-  I feel like I’m the only one eating.  Here, try some.
Thing is, I kept thinking, it didn’t have to be that way.  That the best of Banner and best of Hulk, if they’d worked together, maybe they could’ve stopped Thanos.
For years I treated the Hulk like a disease, something to get rid of. But when I started treating him like the cure...
Eighteen months in the Gamma Lab. I put the brains and the brawn together.  And now look at me. Best of both worlds.
100%, little lady.
Thanks, pal.  Hulk out!
So, Bruce, about what we said-
The time travel do-over?  I don’t know, that’s kind of outside my field of expertise...
You pulled this off.  I remember a time that was impossible, too.
I’m supposed to be on Oprah next week, but I guess I could move things around.
Friday, you up?
I’ve had a mild inspiration, like to see if it checks out.  I would like to run one last sim before we pack it in for the night.  This time, in the shape of a Mobius Strip, inverted.
All right, give me the eigenvalue of that particle, factoring in spectral decomp.  Run it.  That’ll take a second.  And don’t worry if it doesn’t pan out, I’m just kind of...
Shit.
What are you doing up?
First of all, that’s a Mommy word, she coined it.
I just had something on my mind.
Correct.  Great minds think alike. What kind do you want?
You done? Now you are.
Once upon a time, Maguna went to bed.  The end.
Love you tons.
Wow, that’s a lot.
Out like a light.  Don’t know how much she loves you but she loves me three thousand.
That’s up there.
What’re you reading?
A book about composting-
I think I solved it.
Just so we’re both talking about the same thing-
Time travel.
That’s amazing.
Yeah.
And terrifying.
To say the least.
We got really lucky-
I know-
Not everybody did.
I can’t help everybody.
Except, it sort of seems like you can.
Not if I stopped right here.
Tony, trying to get you to stop is one of the few failures of my life.
I could just lock the lab, put it in a trunk, sink it to the bottom of the lake, and go to bed.
But could you rest?
I reran my calculations three times-
I have seven PhD’s, an MD, the Hans Bethe Award for Physics, and I’m personal friends with Bill Nye the Science Guy.  We’re good.
Breakers are set, emergency generator’s on stand-by.
Good.  If we blow the grid, I don’t want to lose Tiny back in the ‘50’s.
He was kidding.
I was kidding.
You were kidding, right?
Honestly, I have no idea.  We’re attempting time travel.  Either it’s all a joke, or none of it is. We’re good!  Helmet on.
Okay.  I’m going to send you back one week, give you an hour to look around, then bring you back in ten seconds.  Make sense?
Good luck, Scott.  You’ve got this.
Counting down from three, two, one...
Is that Scott?
Probably...?
Get him back!
Bruce!  Get it under control.  What the hell is going on?
I got it, I know exactly what’s going on.  Pretty much.
Oh, my God.
It’s a baby.
It’s Scott.
As a baby!
When I tell you, kill the power! Now!
Why the long face?  Wild guess, he turned into a baby?
Among other things.
EPR Paradox.  Instead of pushing Lang through time, you were pushing time through Lang.  It’s dangerous. I probably should’ve cautioned you against it.
You did.
Thank god, I’m here.  Regardless, I fixed it.
That is a fully-functioning, time- space GPS.  I just want peace. Resentment is corrosive.  I hate it.
Me, too.
We’ve got a shot at the Stones.  I just need you to know my priorities.  Bring back everyone we lost, hopefully.  Keep what I found, definitely.  And, let’s not die trying.
Sounds like a deal.
But wait, there’s more.   Act now, and it comes with a bonus offer.
Tony, I don’t know-
What’s to know?  He made it for you.  Plus, I gotta get it out of the garage before Morgan takes it sledding.
Thank you, Tony.
Just don’t flaunt it.  I didn’t bring enough for the whole team. We are getting the whole team, right?
We’re trying.
Hey, Humie.  Where’s Big Green?
Finally.  I ain’t got all day.
I call shotgun!
What the heck are they looking at?
I’m kind of famous...
Yeah, I’m sure that’s it.  Kind of a step down from golden palaces and magic hammers...
They lost Asgard, then half their people.  Maybe they’re just happy to have a home.
Hey, Valkyrie!  Great to see you!
This is Rocket.
Hey.
We didn’t say we were here to see-
We’re definitely here to see him.
It’s that bad?
Something died in here.
Hello...?  Thor...?
Are you here about the cable?
Cinemax went out two days ago, and the sports are all...fuzzy...
Thor?
BROS!  Bring it in!
Yeah, I’m good.
Hulk, you know my boys, Korg and Miek, right?
Hey, guys.  Long time no-
Noobmaster again?

Noobmaster, this is Thor, again. God of Thunder.  This is your last warning.  Log off this game or I will come to your basement, rip off your arms and shove them up your butt.  Right, who wants a drink?
Hey, buddy, are you all right?
Don’t I look all right?
You look like melted ice cream-
So, what’s up?  Just here for a hang?
We need your help.  There’s a chance we can fix everything.
Like the cable?  It’s driving me bananas.
Like Thanos.
Don’t say that name.
Please take your hand off me.
Now, I know the thought of...that guy might scare you-
Scared?  Why would I be scared of that guy?  I’m the one who killed that guy, remember?  Anyone else here kill that guy?
Didn’t think so.  Korg, tell everyone who chopped Thanos’ head off.
Not.  Cool.  Man.
Don’t.  Care.  Dude.
Look, I get it.  You’re in a rough patch.  I’ve been there.  But you know who helped me out of it?
Was it Natasha?
It was you.  You helped me.  And I need you to help me again.
Ask the Asgardians down there how much “my help” is worth.
At least they’re alive-
They were gods!  Now they’re fisherpeople!  The ones that are left, anyway.
That’s the thing.  I think we can bring them back.
Stop.  Stop.  I know you think I’m down here, wallowing in my own self- pity, waiting to be rescued.  But I’m fine.  I’m happy.  Whatever it is you’re offering, don’t care. Couldn’t care less.
Come on, pal.  We need you.
There’s beer in the ship.
What kind?
Neither should you.
That what you’re calling this?
Killing these people isn’t going to bring your family back. We found something.  A chance, maybe...
Don’t what?
I’m just sorry I couldn’t give it sooner.
Out of the way, Lebowski.
Hey, Ratchet, you get lost in there?
It’s Rocket, and shut up.  You’re only a genius on Earth, pal.
And you’re only in there because you have tiny hands.
Fixed it.
Thank you.
Get used to saying that.
I’m being very careful-
Okay, Clint, you might feel a little disoriented when you chronoshift-
Uh, one, because that’s horrible. And, two, killing baby Thanos doesn’t kill adult Thanos.  Time doesn’t work like that.  You can’t change the future by changing the past.
Heard from who?

WHY DOES EVERYONE THINK THIS? THAT’S NOT TRUE.  IF YOU TRAVEL TO THE PAST, THEN THAT PAST HAS BECOME YOUR PRESENT, AND YOUR FORMER PRESENT HAS BECOME THE PAST, WHICH NOW CAN’T BE CHANGED BY YOUR NEW FUTURE!
Okay, Clint.  Starting in three, two, one...
Are you all right?  Hey, look at me.  You okay?
Tell me something good...
Holy crap.  We’re freaking time travelers.
Okay.  Now that we’ve got how, we’re going to need where and when.
Most folks here have encountered at least one of the six Infinity Stones-
I think you mean nearly been killed by one of the six Infinity Stones.
Regardless, we’ve only got enough Pym Particles for one round trip, each.  And the Stones have been in a lot of places throughout history.
Our history.  Not all of them are going to be a fun drop-in.
Exactly.  Let’s start with the Aether.  Thor, what do we know?
Is he asleep?
The Aether’s not a stone, it’s more of an angry sludge.  My grandfather hid it from Dark Elves in a rock between dimensions that can only be accessed every 5000 years.
Or...by Jane.  She stuck her hand in a rock.  Then the Aether stuck itself inside her.  Then I took her to Asgard.  We were dating... We’re not anymore.
Quill said he stole the Power Stone from Morag.
That’s a person?
It’s a planet.  Quill was a person.
Aw, look.  It’s like a puppy, all happy and everything.
You want to go to space, puppy? I’ll take you to space.
And that is...?
So this ‘Time Stone’ guy...what kind of doctor was he?
Strange?
Cross between ear-nose-and-throat and rabbit-from-hat.
Had a nice place in the Village.
Yeah.  Sullivan Street.
Bleecker.
Sullivan and Bleecker.  They’re cross streets.
Wait, he lived in New York?  Guys, pick the right year and there were three stones in New York.
Shut the front door...
Okay, we have a plan.  Six stones, three teams, one shot.
Five years ago, we lost.  All of us.
We lost friends.  We lost family. We lost a part of ourselves. But today we have a chance to take it all back.
You have your teams and you have assignments.  Get your stone, and get back here.  One round trip each.  No mistakes.  No do-overs.

Most of us are going back to places we know.  That doesn’t mean we know what to expect.  Be careful.  Look out for each other.  Improvise, if you have to. This is the fight of our lives. And we’re going to win. Whatever it takes.
He’s pretty good at that...
All right, you heard the man. Stroke those keys, Jolly Green.
Tracking beacons engaged.
You promise to bring that thing back in one piece?
That’s pretty lame, as far as promises go.
See you in a minute.
Actually, it’ll be closer to seven or eight microseconds, give or-
Okay, Park Avenue’s that way. Let’s huddle up.  Suits off.
We’ve all got our assignments.  Two stones uptown, one stone down. Stay low, keep an eye on time-
And Bruce?  Maybe smash a few things along the way.  For appearances.
All right, but I have to say, it seems gratuitous.
Grrr...grrr...
Hulk...does what...Hulk want?
I’m looking for Dr. Strange.
Well, that, actually.
I’m seriously sorry but...I wasn’t asking.
You’re right, I don’t.  But I need that stone, and I don’t have a lot of time to debate it-
No, no, no-
That’s Jane.
Okay, here’s the deal.  You’re going to charm her, and I’m going to poke her with this thing, extract the Reality Stone, and get gone lickety-split.

Um, I’ll be right back.  The wine cellar is just down here.  My father used to have this barrel of Aakonian ale.  Felt like getting hit in the face with a poleaxe. I’ll see if the scullery has a couple of to-go cups-
Who’s the fancy broad?
My mother.  She dies today.
Oh, jeez.
I can’t do this.  This is a bad idea.  I can’t do this...
Come here.

You think you’re the only one who’s lost people?  What do you think we’re doing here?  I lost the only family I ever had.  Quill, Groot, Drax, the chick with the antenna. All gone.  I’ve lived five meaningless years without them, and every minute has blown Aaskvarian gornads.  I get you miss your mom. But she’s gone.  Really gone. There are plenty of people who are only kind of gone.  And you can help them.  So, is it too much to ask that you brush the crumbs out of your beard, make shmoopy talk to Prettypants, and when she’s not looking, suck out the Infinity Stone, and help me get my family back?
I guess not.
Good.
Thank you.  I can do this.
Great.
I can do this...I can do this... I can’t do this...
All right, heartbreaker.  This is our shot...
Thor?
I can kill him, and say the Elves did it.
Yeah, come on, chop chop, we’re on the clock, here.
Take care of yourself.
What?
Further every second.
If it’s all the same to you...I’ll have that drink now.
Cap, I’ve got to say that outfit does nothing for your ass.
No one asked you to look, Tony.
Ball’s in play.  Head’s up, Cap.
Mind Stone’s on the move.
I’m in position.
SHIELD.  Actually, Hydra.  But we didn’t know that yet.
You’re small but you’re talking loud.
All right, you’re up, Little Buddy. There’s our stone.
Okay, Cap, I make ten of them, just passing the 80th floor.
Got it.  Head to the lobby.
Already on my way.
Change of plans.
Rumlow.
I got a call from the Secretary’s office.  I’m going to be running point on the scepter.
We’ve had word there might be an attempt to steal it.
No.  Trust me.  It’s okay...
Hail Hydra.
Okay, Thumbelina, you’re a go.
Yeah, I had a can in the desk for emergencies.  Can we focus, please?
Move it, Stuart Little.  Things are getting dicey out here
You’re only giving me a minor cardiac dysrhythmia-
Window’s closing.  Pull my plug.
Meet me in the alley.  I’m just gonna grab a slice at Famous Ray’s-
Tony?  What’s going on?  Tell me you got that cube-
Oh, great.
I’m not Loki.  And I don’t want to hurt you.
Forgot about that one.
Yeah, I know...
PX.  Camp Lehigh.  1943.
That is America’s ass.
Yeah, with all due respect, I’m not sure the science supports that.
Lady, I just want to borrow your necklace-
No.  But it can erase it.
Because once we’re done with the stones, we can return each one to its own timeline.  At the moment it was taken.  So chronologically, in that reality, the stone never left.
We will.  I will.  I promise.
Yeah?  Then why the hell did Strange give it away?
Strange gave Thanos the Time Stone.
Don’t know.  Maybe he made a mistake.
Then he must have had a reason.
Thank you.
-the Stones have been in a lot of places throughout history.
Our history.  Not all of them are going to be a fun drop-in.
Exactly.  Let’s start here-
Mother!  What?  Nothing.  Hello.
I always wear this.  It’s one of my favorites.
Oh, that.  You remember the...Battle of Harokin.  I took a...broadsword to the face?
Yes, I am-
I didn’t say I was from the future...
I’m totally from the future.
I need to talk to you.
...and then it was done.  His head over there.  Body over there.  And me in the middle.  Just an idiot with an axe.
Yeah, I guess.
That’s a little harsh-
Okay, maybe just stop talking.
I’m not supposed to be like everyone else, though.
I’ve really missed you, Mum.
I got it I got it I got it!
Mum, I have to tell you something-
But your future-
Hi.  You must be Mom. I got the thing.  Come on, we gotta move-
I wish we had more time-
Three...two-
No.  Wait.
What am I looking at?
Still worthy.
Goodbye, Mum.
Oh, fu-
You murdered trillions.
Where are the stones?
You used them two days ago!
We’ve got a problem.
How could you lose it?
What do you want?  I got hit in the head with a Hulk!
You’re not helping-
Okay, okay, Loki’s from Asgard, he’s comfortable there.  Knows the restaurants.  It’s a safe bet he visits home.  If we can just grab This-Thor and explain the situation, he and I can fly-
Loki could be anywhere in the universe.  We’d be old men before we found him.
What other options did we have on the Tesseract?
But if we don’t try, nobody else comes home, either.
I got it!  There’s another way to re-take the Tesseract, and acquire new particles. Military installation, Garden State.
When were they both there?
I have a vaguely exact idea.
How vague?
I know they were there, and I know how I know.
Looks like we’re improvising.
Scott, take this back to the Compound.
All right, suits on.  Try these coordinates. 04-07-19-70...
You trust me?
I do.
You weren’t actually born here, right?
The idea of me was.
All right.  If I was SHIELD and I wanted to hide my quasi-fascistic black site, where would I hide it?
In plain sight.
Good luck with that mission, Captain.
Good luck with your project, Doctor.
Not exactly.
Come on, you little hexahedron, where are you hiding?
You may not know it now, but someday you’re going to be a real pain-in-the-ass.
No.  Haven’t seen a soul.
No, sir.  Just visiting from MIT.
Howard...
Potts.
That’d be swell.
Dr. Pym?
This is Captain Stevens, from shipping.  We have a package for you.
That’s the thing, sir, we can’t.
It’s just...sir, the box is glowing.  And to be honest, a couple of our mail guys aren’t feeling great-
Sauerkraut and a bouquet...big night planned?
Congratulations.
How far along is she?
I have a little girl.
Would that be so bad?
Got any names, yet?
You might let that stew a while. You’ve got time.
Yeah.  I guess.
Wildly.
I pieced it together as I went along.  I thought about what my dad did...
I tried to hold onto the good stuff.  Dad dropped the odd pearl, here and there.
“No amount of money ever bought a second of time.”
He did his best.
You’re going to do fine, Howard.
Count on it...
Yeah.  I’m gonna bet the raccoon didn’t have to climb a mountain.

So was I.  Stay down. Final warning.
I can do this all day.
That shield doesn't belong to you.  You don't deserve it. My father made that shield!
It's just the first pass.
Give me some feedback. Anything you can think of. Shock absorption. Lateral movement. Cup holder?
Let's go. I'll give you a hand.
You okay?

Tony, I'm glad you're back at the compound. I don't like the idea of you rattling around a mansion by yourself. We all need family. The Avengers are yours, maybe more so than mine. I've been on my own since I was 18. I never really fit in anywhere, even in the army. My faith's in people, I guess. Individuals. And I'm happy to say that, for the most part, they haven't let me down. Which is why I can't let them down either. Locks can be replaced, but maybe they shouldn't. I know I hurt you, Tony. I guess I thought by not telling you about your parents I was sparing you, but I can see now that I was really sparing myself, and I'm sorry. Hopefully one day you can understand. I wish we agreed on the Accords, I really do. I know you're doing what you believe in, and that's all any of us can do. That's all any of us should . . .
Yeah, put him through.
Ah, please hold.
So, no matter what. I promise you, if you need us, if you need me, I'll be there.
You sure about this?
Thank you for this.
You know, If they find out he's here . . . they'll come for him.
Underoos!
What are you doing, a little video diary?
It’s all right. I’d probably do the same.
It’s okay.
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey. You know what? We should actually... We should make an alibi video for your aunt anyway. You ready?
We rolling?
Get in the frame.
Hey, May. How you doing? What are you wearing? Something skimpy, I hope.
Peter, that’s inappropriate. All right, let’s start over. You can edit it.
Three, two, one. Hey, May. My gosh, uh, I wanted to tell you what an incredible job your nephew did this weekend at the Stark internship retreat. Everyone was impressed.
This is because you’re not on Queens Boulevard. See, Happy is... is hoping to get bumped up to asset management. He was forehead of security, and before that, he was just a driver.
No, seriously, was he snoring a bunch?
Happy, can you give us a moment?
Why don’t you grab Peter’s case out of the trunk.
Yes, we were just talking about it.
Do me a favor, though. Happy’s kind of your point guy on this. Don’t stress him out. Don’t do anything stupid. I’ve seen his cardiogram. All right?
Don’t do anything I would do, and definitely don’t do anything I wouldn’t do. There’s a... There’s a little grey area in there, and that’s where you operate.
No.
Seventh floor.
What, next mission?
We’ll call you.
No, I mean, we’ll call you. Like, someone will call you.
All right?
Okay.
It’s not a hug. I’m just grabbing the door for you. We’re not there yet.
Bye.
Hi. I’m Captain America. Whether you’re in the classroom or on the battlefield...
...fitness can be the difference between success or failure.
Today, my good friend, your gym teacher...
...will be conducting the Captain America Fitness Challenge.
I put everything in your suit. Including this heater.
What were you thinking?
Take him down now, huh? Steady, Crockett, there are people who handle this sort of thing.
No, no, no. This is a little below their pay grade.
Oh, I’m not here.
Thank God this place has Wi-Fi or you would be toast right now. Thank Ganesh while you’re at it.
Cheers.
Look, forget the flying vulture guy, please.
Why? Because I said so!
Sorry, I’m talking to a teenager. Stay close to the ground. Build up your game helping little people, like that lady that bought you the churro. Can’t you just be a friendly...
...neighborhood Spider-Man?
No, you are not.
Trust me, kid. If Cap wanted to lay you out, he would’ve. Listen to me. If you come across these weapons again, call Happy.
You know, it’s never too early to start thinking about college. I got some pull at MIT.  End call.
So... You got detention. You screwed up.

You know what you did was wrong. The question is, how are you gonna make things right? Maybe you were trying to be cool. But take it from a guy who's been frozen for 65 years, the only way to really be cool is to follow the rules.
We all know what's right. We all know what's wrong. Next time those turkeys try to convince you of something you know is wrong...
Just think to yourself, what would Captain America do?
So your body's changing. Believe me, I know how that feels.
Mr. Parker. Got a sec?
Nice work in D.C.
My dad never really gave me a lot of support... And I’m just trying to break the cycle of shame.
Don’t cut me off when I’m complimenting you. Anyway, great things are about to-
What is that?
That’s odd. Happy told me you quit band six weeks ago. What’s up?
Hey.
Hi, Spider-Man. Band practice, was it?
I think you’ve done enough.

Previously on Peter Screws the Pooch: I tell you to stay away from this. Instead, you hacked a multimillion-dollar suit so you could sneak around behind my back doing the one thing I told you not to do.
No thanks to you.
I did listen, kid. Who do you think called the FBI, huh? Do you know that I was the only one who believed in you? Everyone else said I was crazy to recruit a 14-year-old kid.

No, this is where you zip it, all right? The adult is talking. What if somebody had died tonight? Different story, right? ‘Cause that’s on you. And if you died, I feel like that’s on me. I don’t need that on my conscience.
Yes.
Sorry doesn’t cut it.
And I wanted you to be better. Okay, it’s not working out. I’m gonna need the suit back.
Forever.
Yeah. Yeah, that’s how it works.
Let’s have it.
If you’re nothing without this suit, then you shouldn’t have it. Okay? God, I sound like my dad.
Okay, we’ll sort that out.
If you’re nothing without this suit, then you shouldn’t have it.
Oh, there they are. How was the ride up?
Give me a minute with the kid.
Yeah. I gotta talk to the kid.
How about a loose follow? All right? Boundaries are good.

Sorry I took your suit. I mean, you had it coming. Actually, it turns out it was the perfect sort of tough-love moment that you needed, right? To urge you on, right? Wouldn’t you think? Don’t you think?
Let’s just say it was.

You screwed the pooch hard. Big time. But then you did the right thing. Took the dog to the free clinic, you raised the hybrid puppies... All right, not my best analogy. I was wrong about you. I think, with a little more mentoring, you could be a real asset to the team.
Yeah. Anyway... There’s about fifty reporters behind that door. Real ones, not bloggers.
When you’re ready... Why don’t you try that on? And I’ll introduce the world to the newest official member of the Avengers: Spider-Man.
Yeah. Give that a look.
So, after the press conference, Happy will show you to your room, your new quarters. Where’s he between? He’s next to Vision?
It’s fun.
You’ll fit right in.
You’re good? Good? How are you good?
You turning me down? You better think about this.  Look at that. Look at me. Last chance, yes or no?
Okay. It’s kind of a Springsteen-y, working class hero vibe that I dig. Uh, Happy will take you home. Yeah?
Yes, Mr. Parker. Very well.
Okay.
Yes, you passed. All right, skedaddle there, young buck.
Yeah, thank you.
Where’s the kid?
Everybody’s waiting.
You know what? He actually made a really mature choice. It just surprised the heck out of us.
Did you guys screw this up?
He told the kid to go wait in the car.
Are you kidding me? I have a room full of people in there waiting for some big announcement. What am I gonna tell them?
Think of something. How about, um... Hap, you still got that ring?
The engagement ring?
Okay.
I think I can think of something better than that.
Well, it would buy us a little time.
Like we need time.
I can’t believe you have that thing in your pocket.
Want me to get the door for you, hon?
I got it.

Hi. I’m Captain America. Here to talk to you about one of the most valuable traits a soldier or student can have. Patience. Sometimes patience is the key to victory. Sometimes it leads to very little. It seems like it’s not worth it. And you wonder why you waited so long for something so disappointing.
How many more of these?
This is a nightmare.
I've had better nightmares.
What have we got?
Whatever the signal is sending, it finally creeped off.
I thought we bypassed the battery.
Reboot and send the signal again.
We don't even know what this is.
Fury did. Just do it, please. You tell me the second you get a signal. I want to know who's on the other end of that thing.
Hello, mother. Have I made you proud?
Define worse.
I really don't see what all the fuss is about.
I went down to Midgard to rule the people of Earth as a benevolent god. Just like you.
Give or take 5000 years.
It is my birthright.
If I am for the axe, then for mercy's sake, just swing it. It's not that I don't love our little talks, it's just ... I don't love them.
And what of Thor? You'll make that witless oaf king while I rot in chains?
Is that why everything is on fire?
Hello.  I accept your surrender.
Anyone else?
Hogun, the peace is nearly won across the Nine Realms. You should stay here. Be with your people, where your heart is. Asgard can wait.
As you have mine. Heimdall, when you're ready.
As are Nornheim and Ria. Though our work would have gone more quickly with you at the fore.
That was not my intent.
Thank you.
This isn't about Jane Foster, Father.
I remember you celebrated the battle of Haragon so much that you nearly started a second.
No, this is one I set myself.
I thank you for your sword and for your counsel, good Lady Sif.
Merriment can sometimes be a heavier burden than battle.
Perhaps. How fare the stars?
Yes, the alignment of the worlds. It approaches, doesn't it?
I see nothing.
How is she?
What?
Jane.
Well, I am. Jane...
Where were you? Heimdall could not see you.
I know, I know, but the Bifrost was destroyed. The Nine Realms erupted into chaos, wars were raging, marauding hordes were pillaging. I had to put an end to the slaughter.

Jane, I fought to protect you from the dangers of my world, but I was wrong, I was a fool.  I believe that fate brought us together. Jane, I don't know where you were or what happened, but I do know this.
I know...
Do what?
Space is fine.
Jane! Jane?  You alright?
The woman is unwell.
So am I.
Hold on to me.
This is not of Earth, what is it?
She's ill.
I brought here because we can help her.
Something is within her, father, something I have not seen before.
Don't touch her.  Jane, are you alright?
No, it's defending itself.
"Born of eternal night, the Dark Elves comes to steal away your light." They were these stories mother told us as children.
Are you certain? The Aether was said to have been destroyed with them and yet here it is.
Odin continues to bring me new friends. How thoughtful.
Is that how I'm to while away eternity, reading?
Have you? Does Odin share your concern? Does Thor? It must be so inconvenient them asking after me day and night.
My actions. I was merely giving truth to the lie that I had been fed my entire life, that I was born to be a king.
A mere handful compared to the number that Odin has taken himself.
He's not my father!
You're not.
Well Heimdall had lost sight of you, you were no longer on Earth.

I believe you were in between worlds. The Nine Realms travel within Yggdrasil, orbiting Midgard in much the way your planet orbits the sun. Every five thousand years the worlds align perfectly, we call this the Convergence.  During this time the boarders between worlds become blurred. It's possible you found one of these points. We are lucky that it remained open. Once the worlds pass out of alignment, the connection is lost.
I'll find a way to save you, Jane.
My father doesn't know everything.
Jane Foster, please meet Frigga, the Queen of Asgard, my mother.
You might want to take the stairs to the left.
Loki.
Return to your cells and further harm will come to you. You have my word.  Very well, you don't have my word.
She's your prisoner now?  Leave us.
Nor I with you, but I intend to pursue Malekith.
Yes, and you will destroy us.

No, I value our peoples lives. I'll take Jane to the Dark World and draw the enemy away from Asgard. When Malekith pulls the Aether from Jane it will be exposed vulnerable, and I will destroy it and him.
The risk is far greater if we do nothing. His ship could be over our heads right now and we'd never even know it.
And how of our men shall fall on theirs?
And how are you different from Malekith?
You're not in Odin's war council?
Malekith will return, you know this. I'll need your help.
I'm not asking you to. The Realms need their All-Father strong and unchallenged, whether he is or not. But he is blinded, Heimdall, by hatred and by grief.
Well I see clearly enough.
Everything that we do from here on is a risk, there is no other way.

What I'm about to ask of you is treason of the highest order. Success will bring us exile and failure shall mean our death. Malekith knew the Aether was here, he can sense its power. If we do nothing he will come for it again, but this time lay waste to all of Asgard.  We must move Jane off world.
One, actually.
Thor, after all this time and now you come to visit me. Why? Have you come to gloat? To mock?
Loki, enough. No more illusions.
Now you see me, brother.  Did she suffer?
I did not come here to share our grief. Instead I offer you the chance of a far richer sacrament.
Go on.
I know you seek vengeance as much as I do. You help me escape Asgard and I will grant it to you, vengeance. And afterward, this cell.
You must be truly desperate to come to me for help. What makes you think you can trust me?

I don't. Mother did. You should know that when we fought each other in the past, I did so with a glimmer of hope that my brother was still in there somewhere. That hope no longer exists to protect you. You betray me and I will kill you.
Hmm. When do we start?
He will try.
This is so unlike you, brother. So clandestine. Are you sure you wouldn't rather just punch your way out?
If you keep speaking I just might.
Fine. As you wish. I'm not even here.  Is this better?
Still, we could be less conspicuous.  Hm, brother. You look ravishing.
It will hurt no less when I kill you in this form.

Very well. Perhaps you prefer one of your new companions, given that you seem to like them so much.  Oh, this is much better. Woh. The costume's a bit much, so tight. But the confidence, I can feel the righteousness surging. Hey, you wanna have a rousing discussion about truth, honor, patriotism? God bless Amer–  What?  You could at least furnish me with a weapon. My dagger, something!  At last, a little common sense.
And I thought you liked tricks.
I won't be the one who comes for her.
I'm Loki. You may have heard of...
I like her.
Thank you.
It's good to see you too, Sif.
That, my friend, is where we won't be leaving by foot.
Thank you, my friend.
You'll kill me? Evidently there will be a line.   I thought you said you knew how to fly this thing.
I said, "how hard could it be?"
They're on the ship!  Well, whatever you're doing, brother, I suggest you do it faster.
Shut up, Loki.
You must have missed something.
No, I didn't, I'm pressing every button on this thing.
No, don't hit it, just press it gently.
I am pressing it gently. It's not working!
I think you missed a column.
Shut up!
Look, why don't you let me take over, I'm clearly the better pilot.
Is that right? Well, out of the two of us which one can actually fly?
Oh, dear. Is she dead?
Jane.
Not a word.
Now they're following us.  Now they're firing at us!
Yeah, thank you for the commentary, Loki! It's not at all distracting!

Well done, you just decapitated your grandfather.  You know this is wonderful. This is a tremendous idea. Let's steal the biggest, most obvious ship in the universe and escape in that. Flying around the city, smashing into everything in sight so everyone can see us. It's brilliant, Thor! It's truly brilliant!
You lied to me. I'm impressed.
I'm glad you're pleased. Now, do as you promised. Take us to your secret pathway.  Fandral.
Loki!
If it were easy everyone would do it.
Are you mad?
Possibly.  Ta-da!
What I could do with the power that flows through those veins.
It would consume you.
She's holding up alright, for now.
She's strong in ways you'd never even know.
Say goodbye.
Not this day.
This day, the next, a hundred years, it's nothing. It's a heart beat. You'll never be ready. The only woman whose love you've prized will be snatched from you.
And will that satisfy you?
Satisfaction is not in my nature.
Surrender not in mine.
The son of Odin.
No, not just of Odin! You think you alone were loved of mother? You had her tricks, but I had her trust!
Trust. Was that her last expression? Trust? When you let her die!
What help were you in your cell?
Who put me there? Who put me there?!
You know damn well! You know damn well who!  She wouldn't want us to fight.
Well, she wouldn't exactly be shocked.
I wish I could trust you.
Trust my rage.
Jane.
Alright, are you ready?
I am.  You know this plan of yours is going to get us killed.
Yeah, possibly.
You still don't trust me, brother?
Would you?
No, I wouldn't.

You really think I cared about Frigga, about any of you?  All I ever wanted was you and Odin dead at my feet!  Malekith, I am Loki of Jotunheim and I bring you a gift!  I ask only one thing in return, a good seat from which to watch Asgard burn.
Loki, now!   No!
See you in hell, monster!
No. No, no, no! Oh, you fool, you didn't listen!
I know. I'm a fool. I'm a fool!
Stay with me, okay?
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
Shh.
I'm sorry.
It's okay.  It's alright. I'll tell father what you did here today.
I didn't do it for him.
No!
How? Jane, how?
The Convergence.
Then Malekith would have only possessed it that much sooner.
Jane.
It's not me.
Where are we going?
Why are there so many shoes in here?
Are you well, Erik?
Loki is dead.
Thank you.
Yes, well the alignment is only temporary. He must be in exactly at the right place at the right time.
Not by your hand!
You know with all that power, I thought you would hit harder.
How do I get to Greenwich?
Can those things stop him?
I can.   Malekith!
I've come to accept your surrender.
But you can.

My life. Father, I cannot be King of Asgard. I will protect Asgard and all the realms with my last and every breath, but I cannot do so from that chair. Loki, for all his grave imbalance, understood rule as I know I never will. The brutality, the sacrifice, it changes you. I'd rather be a good man than a great King.
When you speak, do I never hear Mother's voice?  This is not for Jane, Father. She does not know what I came here to say. Now forbid me to see her or say she can rule at my side, it changes nothing.
Loki died with honor, I shall try to live the same. Is that not legacy enough?
I shall try to be.
I know.
Thank you, father.
No. Thank you.
Is that why everything's on fire?
Hello.  I accept your surrender.
Anyone else?
I really don't see what all the fuss is about…
I went down to Midgard to rule the people of Earth as a benevolent God, just like you.
Give or take five thousand years.
It is my birthright!
If I'm for the axe, then for mercy's sake, just swing it. It's not that I don't like our little talks, it's just... I don't love them.
And what of Thor? You'll make that witless oaf King while I rot in chains?
Jane?
I am. Jane—
Where were you? Heimdall could not see you.
I know. I know, but the Bifröst was destroyed. The Nine Realms erupted into chaos. Wars were raging, marauders were pillaging…I had to put an end to the slaughter.
Jane, I fought to protect you from the dangers of my world, but I was wrong. I was a fool. I believe that fate brought us together.
My actions? I was merely giving truth to the lie that I had been fed my entire life…that I was born to be a king.
A mere handful compared to the number that Odin has taken himself.
He's not my father!
You're not.
Thor. After all this time and now you come to visit me. Why? Have you come to gloat? To mock?
Loki, enough. No more illusions.
Now you see me, brother. Did she suffer?
I did not come here to share our grief. Instead, I offer you the chance of a far richer sacrament.
Go on.
I know you seek vengeance as much as I do. You help me escape Asgard, and I will grant it to you. Vengeance. And afterward, this cell.
You must be truly desperate to come to me for help. What makes you think you can trust me?

I don't. Mother did. You should know that when we fought each other in the past, I did so with a glimmer of hope that my brother was still in there somewhere. That hope no longer exists to protect you. You betray me, and I will kill you.
Hm. When do we start?
I'm Loki. You may have heard—
I like her.
Good to see you too, Sif.
You'll kill me? Evidently, there will be a line.

You know, this is wonderful! This a tremendous idea! Let's steal the biggest, most obvious ship in the universe and escape in that! Flying around the city, smash it into everything in sight so everyone can see us! It's brilliant, Thor! It's truly brilliant-
You lied to me. I'm impressed.
If it were easy, everyone would do it.
Are you mad?
Possibly.
You think you alone were loved of Mother? You had her tricks, but I had her trust!
Trust? Was that her last expression, trust? While you let her die?!
What good were you in your cell?
Who put me there? Who put me there?!
You know damn well! You know damn well who!  She wouldn't want us to fight.
Well, she wouldn't exactly be shocked.
I wish I could trust you.
Trust my rage.
I will tell Father what you did here today.
I didn't do it for him.
Not by your hand!
I've come to accept your surrender.
But you can.
Loki died with honour. I shall try to live the same. Is that not legacy enough?
I shall try to be.
I know.
Thank you, Father.
No... thank you.
What’s going on down there, Sam?
If we call Tony…
Even if he did…
We’re on our own.
Another!
Nervous, brother?
Have you ever known me to be nervous?
There was the time in Nornheim...
That wasn't nerves, brother. It was the rage of battle. How else could I have fought my way through a hundred warriors and pulled us out alive?
As I recall, I was the one who veiled us in smoke to ease our escape.
Some do battle, others just do tricks.
Loki...
Now that was just a waste of good wine.
Just a bit of fun. Right, my friend?
Nice feathers.
You don't really want to start this again, do you, Cow?
I was being sincere!
You're incapable of sincerity.
Am I?
I've looked forward to this day as long as you have. You're my brother and my friend. Sometimes I'm envious, but never doubt that I love you.
Thank you.
Give us a kiss.
Stop.
How do I look?
Like a king.
It's time.
You go ahead.
I'll be along. Go on.
Why does everyone keep saying that? I'm not nervous!
...but never you. I know.
And what is that?
He said he'd be along.
I wouldn't worry. Father will forgive him. He always does.
I swear.
I swear.
I swear.
The Jotuns must pay for what they've done!
All is well?! They broke into the Weapons Vault! If the Frost Giants had stolen even one of these RELICS--
I want to know why they--
And if you hadn't taken it from them they would have laid waste to all the Nine Realms!
He just broke your truce! We must act!
March into Jotunheim as you once did, teach them a lesson, break their spirits so they'll never dare try to cross our borders again!
This was an act of war!
They got this far!
As King of Asgard, I would--
It's unwise to be in my company right now, brother.
Who said I was wise?
This was to be my day of triumph.

It will come. In time. If it's any consolation, I think you're right. About the Frost Giants, about Laufey, everything. If a few of them could penetrate the defenses of Asgard once, who's to say they won't try again. Next time with an army?
Yes, exactly!
But there's nothing we can do without defying Father.
No... stop there! I know that look!
It's the only way to ensure the safety of our borders.
It's madness!
Nothing! Thor was making a jest!
The safety of our Realm is no jest. We're going to Jotunheim.
My father fought his way into Jotunheim, defeated their armies, and took their Casket! We'd just be looking for answers.
My friends, have you forgotten all that we've done together?
Who brought you into the sweet embrace of the most exotic maidens in all of Yggdrasil?
Who led you into the most glorious of battles... ...and to delicacies so succulent, you thought you'd died and gone to Valhalla?
And who proved wrong all who scoffed at the idea that a young maiden could be one of the fiercest warriors this Realm has ever known?
True. But I supported you... My friends, trust me now. We must do this.
Come on. You're not going to let my brother and me take all the glory, are you?
What?
You are coming with me...
Yes, of course! I won't let my brother march into Jotunheim alone. I will be at his side.
We must first find a way to get past Heimdall.
Keep your weapons sheathed and your mouths closed. This is going to take subtlety and sincerity, not brute strength. Leave it to me.
GOOD HEIMDALL--
I'm sorry?
You must be mistaken. We're not--
Enough. Heimdall, may we pass?
Then tell no one where we've gone until we've returned.
Get me off this bridge before it cracks under your girth.
I have no plans to die today.
Come on. Don't be bashful.
Come on, big fella. Up...!
Too late now.
Perhaps we should wait.
For what?
To survey the enemy. To gauge their strengths and weaknesses from a distance.
We know all we must. It's time to act.
It feels good, doesn't it? To be together again, adventuring on another world?
What would you call it?
How about a song to lift our spirits?
Hiding. As cowards always do.
I speak only to your King. Not to his foot soldiers.
And I am--
I demand answers.
How did your people get into Asgard?
Do not dishonor my father's name with your lies.
Not when you'd use it to make war against other Realms.
This boy has grown tired of your mockery.
Thor, stop and think. Look around you. We are outnumbered.
Know your place, brother...
We will accept your most gracious offer.
Damn.
Next!
Pathetic.
Come on! At least make it a challenge for me!
Now that's more like it!
Ugly and stupid.
Come on!
That can't be good.
Thor, we must go!
Then go!
I can stop them!
Likely killed us all!
Loki, we have to see.
Now! We'll finish them together!
Why did you bring us back?
I was protecting my home.
There won't be a kingdom to protect if you're afraid to act!
Whatever the cost, the world must know that the new King of Asgard will not be held in contempt.
While you wait and be patient, the Nine Realms laugh at us! The old ways are done. You'd stand giving speeches while Asgard falls!
And you are an old man and a fool!
FATHER--
Hammer...
Father! Heimdall! I know you can hear me! Open the bridge!
You! What world is this?
Where am I?! Answer me!
What Realm?! Alfheim? Nornheim?
You dare threaten Thor with so puny A--
How dare you attack the son of Odin!
Then bring me a healing stone, you savages!
You're no match for the Mighty--
It's not possible.
Blue sky... one sun... This is Earth, isn't it?
I told him.
I told him to go to Odin after we'd left. Though he should be flogged for taking so long.
I saved our lives! And Thor's. I had no idea Father would banish him for what he did.

And if I do, then what? I love Thor more dearly than any of you, but you know what he is. He's arrogant. He's reckless. He's dangerous. You saw how he was today. Is that what Asgard needs from its King?
Am I cursed?
What am I?
What more than that?
The Casket wasn't the only thing you took from Jotunheim that day, was it?
Laufey's son...
Why? You were knee-deep in Jotun blood. Why would you take me?
You took me for a purpose, what was it?
Tell me!
So I am no more than another stolen relic, locked up here until you might have use of me.
You could have told me what I was from the beginning. Why didn't you?
Because I am the monster parents tell their children about at night?
It all makes sense now. Why you favored Thor all these years.
Because no matter how much you claim to "love" me, you could never have a Frost Giant sitting on the Throne of Asgard!
Guards!
They will suffice.
What does anyone do in the Bifrost?
This mortal form has grown weak.
So why did he lie?
How long will it last?
I never get used to seeing him like this. The most powerful being in the Nine Realms lying helpless until his body is restored.
What hope is there for Thor?
This drink. I like it.
Another!
It was delicious. I want another.
I just did.
I meant no disrespect.
You have my word.
Where?!
Twelve miles east of here.
To get what belongs to me.
It's not what they say it is.
Yes.
If you take me there now, I'll tell you everything you wish to know.
All the answers you seek will be yours, once I reclaim Mjolnir.
I understand. Then this is where we say goodbye.
Jane Foster... Erik Selvig... Darcy. Farewell.
My friends... you haven't heard? I am now Ruler of Asgard.
Father's fallen into the Odinsleep. My mother fears he may never awaken again.
She has refused to leave my father's bedside. You can bring your "urgent" matter to me, your King.
My first command can not be to undo the Allfather's last. We're on the brink of war with Jotunheim. Our people must have a sense of continuity in order to feel safe in these difficult times.
All of us must stand together, for the good of Asgard.
I need a horse.
Then give me one of those, large enough to ride.
Many times. You're brave to do it.
But you're clever. Far more clever than anyone else in this Realm.
You think me strange?
Good strange or bad strange?
You'll see soon enough.
What you seek -- it's a bridge.
More like a rainbow bridge.
You're going to need this.
Stay here. Once I have Mjolnir, I will return what they stole from you.
Deal?
No.
I'm going to fly out.
You're big.
Fought bigger.
Just a man.
I thought he'd never leave.
Loki? What are you doing here?
I had to see you.
What's happened? Tell me! Is it Jotunheim? Let me explain to FATHER--
Father is dead.
What?
Your banishment, the threat of a new war, it was too much for him to bear.
You mustn't blame yourself. I know that you loved him. I tried to tell him so, but he wouldn't listen.
It was cruel to put the hammer within your reach, knowing you could never lift it.
The burden of the throne has fallen to me now.
Can I come home?
The truce with Jotunheim is conditional upon your exile.
But couldn't we find a way to--
Mother has forbidden your return.
This is goodbye, brother. I'm so sorry.
No, I'm sorry. Loki... thank you for coming here.
Nothing could have stopped me.
Fare well, brother.
Good-bye.
Where are we going?
I've come alone and unarmed.
To make you another proposition.
You're welcome.
You have no idea what I am.
Hello, Father.
No longer weak. I now rule Asgard, until Odin awakens. Perhaps you should not have so carelessly abandoned me.
I will conceal you and a handful of your soldiers, lead you into his chambers, and let you slay him where he lies. I'll keep the throne, and you will have the Casket.
When all is done, we will have a permanent peace between our two worlds. Then I, the bastard son, will have accomplished what Odin and Thor never could.
No. Asgard is mine. The rest of the Nine Realms will be yours, if you do as you're told.
What troubles you, Gatekeeper?
Perhaps your senses have weakened after your many years of service.
You have great power, Heimdall. Tell me, did Odin ever fear you?
And why is that?
Exactly. Just as you're sworn to obey me now. Yes?
Good. Then you will open the Bifrost to no one until I have undone what my brother has started.
Thank you for what you've done.
Are you in love with her?
Neither did I.
I swear to you, I mean her no harm.
I had it all backwards. I had it all wrong.
For the first time in my life, I have no idea what I'm supposed to do.
I have no quarrel with you. But she's a lady. You should be more respectful.
I will not fight him.
He's fine. Not injured at all.
Sorry, my friend.
We drank. We fought. He made his ancestors proud.
These are your chambers?
You've been very kind. I've been far less grateful than you deserve.
It was all I could get back. Not as much as I promised. I'm sorry.
What's wrong?
You must do this. You must finish what you've started.
Because you're right. It's taken so many generations for your people to get to this point. You're nearly there. You just need someone to show you how close you really are.
Look -- your ancestors called it magic. You call it science. I come from a place where they're one and the same thing.

This is how my father explained it to me... Your world is one of the Nine Realms of the Cosmos, linked to each other by the branches of Yggdrasil, the Worlds Tree. Now, you see it every day, without realizing. Images glimpsed through - - what did you call it?... this Hubble Telescope. So, Nine Realms...
You're very welcome.
May I have this?
Thank you. Excuse me a moment.
To replace the one I broke. Please forgive my behavior.
If I may, I'd like to come back for more of your "coffee."

You think the Bifrost is the only way in and out of the Realm? There are secret paths between worlds to which even you with all your gifts are blind. But I have need of them no longer, now that I am King. And I say, for your act of treason, you are relieved of your duties as Gatekeeper. And you are no longer a citizen of Asgard.
Ensure my brother does not return.
My friends!
My friends, I've never been happier to see anyone. But you should not have come.
You know I can't. My father is dead because of me. I must remain in exile.
Leave this town now. Get yourself and your friends to safety.
I must stay and fight.
I'm still a warrior, and I will fight by your side.
You're right.
Help me clear the streets. I'll let none of these people die this day.
Father. Welcome to Asgard.
My friends fight bravely, but they won't be able to hold it back much longer.
Come on... give me one!
Go, while you can!
You can't help them now. Your job is to survive.
Live and tell those stories yourself.
Get him out of here!
But not win. Move Volstagg, or he'll die!
Don't worry, my friends. I have a plan.
Brother... for whatever I have done to wrong you, whatever I have done to lead you to do this, I am sorry. But these people have done nothing to you. They are innocents.
Take my life, and know I will never return to Asgard.
Heimdall! Open the Bifrost!
He would open it if he could. I fear the worst.
Heimdall!
Know this, son of Coul. You and I, we fight for the same cause -- the protection of this world. From this day forward, count me as your ally. If you return the items you have stolen from Jane Foster.
Whatever fate lies before me, you are part of it.
Get him to the healing room! Leave my brother to me.
And your death came by the son of Odin.
I swear to you, mother, they will pay for what they've done today. I will end the Jotun threat, now and forever!
And I will make you proud.
Found its way back to you, did it?
No thanks to you.
Why don't you tell her? How you sent the Destroyer to kill our friends? To kill me?
It must have been enforcing Father's last command.
You're a talented liar, brother. Always have been.
It's good to have you back. Now, if you'll excuse me, I need to destroy Jotunheim.
Jotunheim...
All these years, and no one's ever dared to use it as a weapon.
You can't stop it. The Bifrost will build until it rips Jotunheim apart.
Why have you done this?
To do what Father never could. To destroy their kind forever. When he awakens, he'll see the wisdom of what I've done.
He won't! You can't kill an entire race!
What is this newfound love for the Frost Giants? You, who would have killed them all with your bare hands.
I've changed.
So have I.
Fight me.
Is the throne really worth what you've done? What you would become?
I never wanted the throne. I only wanted to be your equal. Now fight me!
I will not fight you, brother.
I am not your brother. I never was.
Loki, this is madness...
Is it?
What happened to you on earth that turned you so soft? Don't tell me it was a woman.
It was.
If you care so much for the Jotuns, then die with them.
Thor! Help me!
Please...
I was always more clever than you.
Yet still not clever enough.
Look at you, the Mighty Thor. With all your strength, what good does it do you now?
Stop! What are you doing?!
If you destroy the Bridge, you'll never see her again!
Forgive me.
No!
There will never be a wiser king than you. Or a better father. I have much to learn. I know that now. But some day, perhaps, I will make you proud.
Can you see her?
How is she?
